A senior Buffalo City Metro manager was hired for a -million-a-year position despite allegedly not meeting all the requirements for the top post. Fikiswa Jakeni-Gomba was given the nod as BCM municipal health services general manager earlier this year.This despite her not being registered with the Health Professions Council of SA (HPCSA), the council s inspector Mamadiga Mamabolo claimed yesterday.For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions